{"source_hash": "ac827584ce011ce6", "candidate": {"id": "cand-025", "name": "R\u00faair\u00ed McCarthy", "raw_cv": "R\u00daAIR\u00cd MCCARTHY\nruairi.mccarthy@email.com | Dublin, Ireland (open to London relocation)\n\nSOFTWARE ENGINEER\n\nPROFESSIONAL SUMMARY\nSoftware engineer with 3 years of experience building Python and TypeScript backends for e-commerce and logistics platforms. Strong fundamentals, growing ownership of technical design. Currently completing a part-time MSc in Distributed Systems.\n\nEXPERIENCE\n\nSoftware Engineer \u2014 Shopify (Dublin office) (2022\u2013present)\n- Backend engineer on the inventory and fulfilment team (Ruby on Rails, Python services)\n- Built the multi-location inventory reservation service handling 2M+ daily checkout events\n- Introduced async task processing (Sidekiq \u2192 Temporal migration) for order orchestration workflows\n- On-call rotation participant; reduced MTTR on inventory alerts from 45 to 12 minutes\n\nJunior Software Engineer \u2014 Intercom, Dublin (2021\u20132022)\n- Built API integrations for the customer data platform (Node.js, TypeScript)\n- Contributed to the Messenger inbox improvements that shipped to 25,000+ companies\n\nSKILLS\nPython, Ruby, TypeScript, Node.js, PostgreSQL, Redis, Kafka (consumer), Temporal, Docker, Git, REST APIs\n\nEDUCATION\nMSc Distributed Systems \u2014 University College Dublin (part-time, 2023\u2013present, expected 2025)\nBSc Computer Science \u2014 Trinity College Dublin (2018\u20132021), First Class Honours\n\nRIGHT TO WORK\nIrish/EU citizen, UK right to work (no sponsorship required)", "raw_linkedin": "Software engineer at Shopify Dublin working on inventory and fulfilment. I write Python and Ruby services that have to be correct under high concurrency \u2014 distributed systems problems are what I find most interesting. I'm three years into my career and I'm doing a part-time MSc in distributed systems at UCD to complement the practical experience. EU citizen with UK right to work. Considering a move to London to be closer to the fintech and infrastructure scene. Looking for a mid-level backend role with real technical depth.", "raw_interview_transcript": "Interviewer: R\u00faair\u00ed, thanks for coming over from Dublin. Tell me about the inventory reservation service.\n\nR\u00faair\u00ed: The problem is classic distributed systems: at checkout, you need to reserve inventory atomically across multiple warehouse locations, and you have to handle concurrent requests for the same SKU without overselling. The naive approach \u2014 select then update \u2014 doesn't work at scale. I built a service using optimistic concurrency control with a version counter on each inventory record, which lets us do high-throughput writes without locking. The tricky part was the rollback path when a checkout fails after reservation.\n\nInterviewer: You mentioned Temporal in your CV. How did that come up?\n\nR\u00faair\u00ed: We had an order orchestration pipeline built with Sidekiq for async jobs, and it was getting hard to reason about failures \u2014 jobs would fail, retries would happen, and the state was spread across multiple tables. I proposed migrating to Temporal for the orchestration layer. It took a few months but we now have much cleaner visibility into workflow state and the retry logic is declarative rather than implicit.\n\nInterviewer: This is a senior-level role \u2014 how do you feel about that step up?\n\nR\u00faair\u00ed: I think I'm ready for more ownership. At Shopify I've been leading the technical design for my team's features for the past year, but the formal seniority jump hasn't happened yet. I'm looking for somewhere that will give me that formal responsibility.\n\nInterviewer: You'd need to relocate to London. Is that genuinely on the table?\n\nR\u00faair\u00ed: Yes. I've been thinking about it for a while \u2014 I want to be in a bigger tech market and London is the obvious move from Dublin.\n\nInterviewer: Salary?\n\nR\u00faair\u00ed: I'm at \u20ac85,000. For London I'd be looking at \u00a380\u201388,000.", "years_experience": 3.0, "skills": ["Python", "Ruby", "TypeScript", "Node.js", "PostgreSQL", "Redis", "Kafka", "Temporal", "Docker", "Git", "REST APIs", "Distributed Systems", "Backend Engineering", "Async Task Processing", "Optimistic Concurrency Control"], "industries": ["e-commerce", "logistics", "fintech", "saas", "infrastructure"], "seniority_level": "mid", "management_experience": false, "education_level": "master", "career_trajectory": "ascending", "interview_score": 0.82, "culture_fit_score": 0.78, "constraints": [{"id": "e5ffe2b9", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "visa", "description": "Irish/EU citizen with UK right to work; no sponsorship required", "canonical_key": "visa_sponsorship", "value": false, "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.98, "currency": null}, {"id": "66dc46c5", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "location", "description": "Open to London relocation from Dublin; considering move to be closer to fintech and infrastructure scene", "canonical_key": "location_city", "value": "London", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.85, "currency": null}, {"id": "425acd5d", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Minimum salary expectation for London role: \u00a380,000", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 80000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.94, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "33a94c23", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Maximum salary expectation for London role: \u00a388,000", "canonical_key": "salary_max", "value": 88000.0, "operator": "max", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.94, "currency": "GBP"}, {"id": "67d79969", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "compensation", "description": "Current salary in Dublin: \u20ac85,000", "canonical_key": "salary_min", "value": 85000.0, "operator": "min", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.95, "currency": "EUR"}, {"id": "32a69c5a", "type": "hard", "side": "candidate", "category": "role_type", "description": "Seeking mid-level to senior backend role with formal responsibility and technical depth; ready for seniority step up with ownership", "canonical_key": null, "value": "mid-senior backend engineer with technical ownership", "operator": "requires", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.9, "currency": null}, {"id": "9c01541d", "type": "soft", "side": "candidate", "category": "industry", "description": "Interested in fintech and infrastructure sectors", "canonical_key": "industry_background", "value": "fintech or infrastructure", "operator": "prefers", "weight": 1.0, "confidence": 0.82, "currency": null}]}, "embedding": [-0.034637451171875, -0.000881195068359375, 0.01505279541015625, -0.0024776458740234375, -0.0168609619140625, 0.003032684326171875, 0.0090179443359375, 0.077392578125, 0.01349639892578125, -0.00484466552734375, -0.006626129150390625, -0.0218048095703125, -0.044525146484375, 0.01409912109375, 0.04803466796875, 0.01424407958984375, -0.0506591796875, -0.025238037109375, -0.01534271240234375, 0.025482177734375, -0.0181732177734375, -0.00818634033203125, -0.004123687744140625, 0.0011358261108398438, 0.0097503662109375, 0.0038814544677734375, -0.0260162353515625, -0.0176544189453125, -0.033843994140625, -0.0236053466796875, 0.035491943359375, -0.0277557373046875, -0.0276031494140625, 0.02508544921875, 0.03814697265625, -0.03076171875, -0.0043487548828125, -0.001979827880859375, 0.0159912109375, -0.012451171875, -0.051055908203125, -0.032562255859375, 0.03704833984375, -0.015380859375, -0.01194000244140625, -0.034088134765625, -0.0261383056640625, -0.01056671142578125, 0.025482177734375, 0.015716552734375, -0.0154571533203125, -0.0283966064453125, -0.017974853515625, 0.048095703125, 0.0005922317504882812, 0.00830841064453125, 0.0058135986328125, 0.0250701904296875, 0.0179290771484375, 0.01727294921875, 0.043792